s the source of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNAnnotation","role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"type":"topic","title":"MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointCollection":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointcollection","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointCollection","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disconnected vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"points in the collection may be related but are not connected spatially. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use a point collection to represent all the trees in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"orchard."}],"title":"MLNPointCollection","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolyline":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolyline","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNPolyline","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of two or more vertices,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the line segments that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"path along which something moves."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolygon":{"abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polygons that do not overlap. For example, you could use a multipolygon shape","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to represent the body of land that consists of an island surrounded by an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll: the inner island would be one "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference"},{"text":" object, while the surrounding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"atoll would be another. You could also use a multipolygon shape to represent a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group of disconnected but related buildings.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolygon","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNMultiPolygon","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolygon"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"fragments":[{"text":"MLNMultiPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"title":"MLNMultiPolyline","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/intersectsOverlayBounds:":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/intersectsoverlaybounds:","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns a Boolean indicating whether the specified rectangle intersects the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"receiver’s shape.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"intersectsOverlayBounds:","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"- ","kind":"text"},{"text":"intersectsOverlayBounds:","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"intersectsOverlayBounds:","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/intersectsOverlayBounds:","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","title":"overlayBounds","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/coordinate":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/coordinate","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/coordinate","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A coordinate representing the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"fragments":[{"text":"coordinate","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"coordinate"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertices, specified as "},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the edges that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon","title":"MLNPolygon","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"}]}}}